Hi Adolfo,

I am also not entirely sure I completely understand what you ask, but I think you are asking whether the client-server HTTP connection persists after a 202 Response?

The HTTP Interaction regarding 202 would be something like this:


-&gt; POST /orders
   &lt;order&gt;&lt;item id=&quot;10&quot;/&gt;&lt;/order&gt;

&lt;- 202 Accepted
   Location /pending-orders/19
   &lt;order processingStatus=&quot;pending&quot;/&gt;


Client then periodically polls /pending-orders/19:


-&gt; GET /pending-orders/19

&lt;- 200 Ok
   &lt;order processingStatus=&quot;pending&quot;/&gt;

[wait]

-&gt; GET /pending-orders/19

&lt;- 200 Ok
   &lt;order processingStatus=&quot;pending&quot;/&gt;

[wait]

&gt; GET /pending-orders/19

&lt;- 301 Moved Permanently
   Location: /orders/188


-&gt; GET /orders/188

&lt;- 200 Ok
   &lt;order id=&quot;188&quot;&gt;&lt;item id=&quot;10&quot;/&gt;&lt;/order&gt;

The client or server can close the TCP connection between any of these requests.

Does that help?

Jan



